  "prompt": "Which enzyme uses both NAD+ and NADP+ as a coenzyme?",
  "response": "The enzyme Glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase (G6PD) is known to utilize both NAD+ and NADP+ as coenzymes. G6PD plays a crucial role in the pentose phosphate pathway by catalyzing the oxidation of glucose-6-phosphate to 6-phosphoglucono-\u03b4-lactone, reducing NADP+ to NADPH in the process. While its primary coenzyme is NADP+, it has been shown that G6PD can also use NAD+ under certain conditions.",
